description: Vaphne Blinkly is an undergraduate student in Gina's advanced archaeology class at Georgia State University in the Gold Digger universe. She is pursuing a double major in genealogy and anthropology with focuses in extraplanar genealogy and ero-physiologic anthropology (the history of sex). She is the avatar of an ancient Germanic fertility goddess, even though she is still a virgin. She does not get along very well with the goddess Venus living in artifacts belonging to her fellow student Paul Ulysses.
name: Vaphne Blinkly

deck: undergraduate student in Gina's advanced archaeology class in the Gold Digger universe
description: Shoobi Roberts is an undergraduate student in Gina's advanced archaeology class at Georgia State University in the Gold Digger universe. He is majoring in mechanical engineering, and is an expert in ectoplasma-dynamic physics and ethereal engineering. His eyesight enables him to see ethereal energy... like dead people. This has made him naturally a little jumpy.
name: Shoobi Roberts

deck: undergraduate student in Gina's advanced archaeology class in the Gold Digger Universe
description: Anton Fist is an undergraduate student in Gina's advanced archaeology class at Georgia State University in the Gold Digger Universe. He already has a masters degree in physics, and is now majoring in parapsychology with a minor in archaeology. He was the former president of the campus Science League, and is current president of the campus Ghost Hunter Society. He prefers to approach archaeology using technology and hard science rather than the intuitive approach of his fellow students Aljabra Gihom and Elroy Nabbum.
name: Anton Fist

deck: Paul Barrett is an attorney in Central City who was hypnotized by Mirror Master (Scudder) to aid him in his crimes.
description:
Creation

Paul Barrett made his first appearance in The Flash #130 - Who Doomed the Flash? He was created by Carmine Infantino and John Broome

Character History

Paul Barrett is an attorney in the Central City who had been representing Mirror Master (Scudder) in court. During the trail of Mirror Master, Barrett was hypnotized by Scudder, who used a series of small mirrors to put Barrett under his control.

Barrett began listening to Scudder's orders and aided him in several schemes. Utilizing a variety of costumes such as Trickster's, Top's and Captain Boomerang's he made Flash believe that the heroes he had jailed had somehow broken out.

Eventually Barrett encountered Flash and used some sort of smoke/gas to knock Flash out. He then stole Flashes costume and delivered it to Mirror Master who switched places with Barrett, thus letting Scudder out of jail while Barrett was left in the cell.

Once he had recovered from Mirror Master's control he was able to help the true Flash by telling him where Scudder's next target was, a memory still in the back of his mind due to Scudder's mental manipulations.
